cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper focuses on the development of a fully decentralized control infrastructure for collaborative transport using small unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs). This falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of a swarm-specific scripting language, Buzz, also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions testing the performance of their approach with a fleet of micro-UAVs, which could involve computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for navigation and obstacle avoidance.
